        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 6 at 9:24PM MDT until July 6 at 10:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>SVRGLD

The National Weather Service in Goodland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Sherman County in northwestern Kansas...

* Until 1015 PM MDT.

* At 924 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles north of
Goodland, moving south at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Goodland around 930 PM MDT.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 9 and 34.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
